text: Kees Witteveen, also written as Cees Witteveen, (14 February 1871 â€“ 23 March 1927) was a Dutch cyclist who was active in the 1890s. He won the silver medal in the amateur motor-paced event at the 1895 ICA Track Cycling World Championships. He won at the Dutch National Road Race Championships the silver medal in 1891, 1894 and 1895. == References == Category:1871 births Category:1927 deaths Category:Dutch cyclists
